'''''Mutineers''''' is the 10th studio album by English singer-songwriter [[David Gray (musician)|David Gray]], released on 17 June 2014 on [[IHT Records]]. "Back in the World" was the first single for the album.

==Background==
On 1 April 2014, the video for "Gulls" was premiered on both the Myles O'Reilly website [http://arbutusyarns.net arbutusyarns.net] and David's official YouTube channel, with Myles being the director.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iF-xx8mMWIo|title=David Gray - Gulls (Official Video)|first=|last=David Gray|date=1 April 2014|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://arbutusyarns.net/2014/04/01/david-gray-gulls/|title=David Gray :: Gulls|date=1 April 2014|publisher=}}</ref>

On 10 April 2014, "Back in the World" from the new album Mutineers was uploaded onto David's official YouTube channel.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KFGdK2GAXVU|title=David Gray – Back In The World (Audio)|first=|last=David Gray|date=10 April 2014|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref> A day later, the track was played back by radio presenter [[Chris Evans (presenter)|Chris Evans]] on [[BBC Radio 2]] for ''[[The Chris Evans Breakfast Show]]'' at exactly 7:45am. Gray reported that he would be visiting Chris 'down the road' during the starting of the tour for the album at the week of release for Radio 2.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://instagram.com/p/mp6s99D_rY/|title=Instagram photo by David Gray • Apr 11, 2014 at 3:41pm UTC|publisher=}}</ref>

